Astro-Coord-Constellations

A module to identify the constellation to which a celestial position (as defined by
equatorial coordinates for any epoch) belongs to, according to the IAU constellation
boundaries.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Astro::Coord::Constellations

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Astro-Coord-Constellations

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Astro-Coord-Constellations

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/Astro-Coord-Constellations

    GitHub
        https://github.com/dkechag/Astro-Coord-Constellations

